##### **Create Your Better Tomorrow**


With over 50 years of experience in the industry, Kollmorgen, a Regal Rexnord brand, is a technology leader in navigation and fleet control of automated guided vehicles (AGVs) and autonomous mobile robots (AMRs). As part of our continue effort to innovate and grow, we are now expanding and are seeking talents to join us and be part of our success story.


Our definition of success goes beyond customer satisfaction; it includes fostering the talent of tomorrow. At Kollmorgen, we cultivate a collaborative and inclusive environment where innovation thrives and every individual is valued. Our commitment to professional growth and development ensures that you will have the opportunity to advance your career while working on cutting-edge automation solutions.

##### **We are looking for a Junior Software Engineer to be part of a dynamic team that is passionate about making a difference in the world of AGVs and AMRs. This is a temporary position from March 2025 to December 2025.**

##### **Position Overview**


Services team plays a crucial role in supporting our partners by providing comprehensive training, consulting, and support services. Additionally, the team is integral to our CI/CD pipeline, conducting thorough testing and evaluation of new technologies requested by customers. The team also interfaces with and utilizes our customer-facing APIs to enhance our software solutions.  





As a Junior Software Engineer, you will be part of the Services team dedicated to driving customer satisfaction and ensuring the optimal use of our product portfolio. You will contribute to software development by coding, testing, implementing solutions while improving your skills through supervised tasks, bug fixes and participation in agile practices. Moreover, you will engage in problem-solving for support cases and play an active role in refining our development processes to deliver innovative and reliable solutions to our partners.

 **What does success look like in this position****:**

* **Innovation and Technical Enhancement:** Engage in the CI/CD process by identifying areas for improvement, conducting through tests and ensuring the seamless integration of customer-requested technologies;
* **Team Collaboration:** Actively participate in team discussions, contribute to collaborative projects, meet deadlines and support the collective success of the team;
* **Solution Development:** Involve yourself in use-case modeling and the breakdown of functional requirements, also contributing to the development of innovative software solutions;
* **Skill Development:** Continuously enhance your technical and professional skills through on-the-job learning, exposure to new technologies, and collaboration with experienced team members.

##### **To achieve the mission and success of this position, we believe you already have:**

* Educational background in Computer science, IT, Engineering, or equivalent;
* Practical experience working in C# or C++;
* Fluency in English, both spoken and written;
* Commitment to high standards and continuous quality improvement;
* Willingness to try new approaches and learn from failures;

##### **We find it beneficial if you have:**

* Familiarity with additional programming languages


We see that our ideal candidates are committed to personal & professional growth, and they share our core values and genuine enthusiasm for innovation.



##### **Additional Information**


Fixed-Term employment from March 2025 to December 2025 | Based in Mölndal, Sweden


Selection takes place on an ongoing basis, so be sure to apply early. We're excited to hear from you!  





##### **Kollmorgen - Autonomous Mobile Solutions**


We offer a complete automation solution for AGV and AMR providers. Our NDC Solutions platform is a proven platform that enables efficient and reliable vehicle automation with increased performance. It includes all hardware, software, and navigation technologies necessary to automate a vehicle fleet. The platform has been installed in a vast variety of material handling sites and vehicles across the globe.
